<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1752,2029]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1752,1777]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Description</emphasis>
: This group is morphologically distinct in the 5–6-toothed mandible of the females (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1344,1752,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6–21. Clypeus and mandibles of females. 6: M. foersteri. 7: M. incana. 8: M. blepharis sp. nov.. 9: M. cinnamomea. 10: M. saussurei. 11: M. nigripes. 12: M. seraxensis. 13: M. ericetorum. 14: M. sanguinipes. 15 (hairs removed on left): M. maxschwarzi sp. nov.. 16 (hairs removed on left): M. flavipes. 17 (hairs removed on left): M. tecta. 18: M. cinnamomea. 19, 20 (profile): M. farinosa. 21: M. riyadhensis (profile). CT: clypeal tooth, APA: apical premarginal area of mandible, HT: clypeal hair tuft, FC: facial comb of hairs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610532/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
), and in a number of conspicuous characteristics of the male such as the absence of the front coxal spine and the presence of a large, acute lateral tooth on T6 (
<figureCitation box="[528,629,1824,1849]" captionStart="FIGURES 120–124" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1302,1325]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,481,1281]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1435,481,1281]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 120–124. Diagnostic traits of M. blepharis sp. nov., males. 120: habitus (dorsal view). 121: habitus (lateral view). 122: vertex. 123: metasoma (posterior view). 124: habitus (facial view). LT: lateral tooth, PAC: preapical carina, AMS: apicomedial spine, GF: gonoforceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610552/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 123</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[641,687,1824,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 125–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1864,1887]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 125–133. Diagnostic traits of M. plumigera sp. nov.. 125: holotype female (facial view). 126: holotype female (lateral view). 127: habitus of male (facial view). 128: habitus of male (lateral view). 129: underside of metasoma of male. 130: vertex of female. 131: vertex of male. 132: genital capsule of male. 133: segments of hind leg of female M. incana (lateral view). LT: lateral tooth, PAC: preapical carina, AMS: apicomedial spine, PVBMS: basomedial spine of penis valve, PVBLA: basolateral angle of penis valve, GF: gonoforceps" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610554/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">129</figureCitation>
). The group shares a number of common morphological traits with the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1845" box="[192,326,1861,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanipennis">
<emphasis box="[192,326,1861,1884]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">cyanipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1937" box="[381,533,1860,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodoleucura">
<emphasis box="[381,533,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">rhodoleucura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups: in the female sex, these traits include the short robust mandible, with surface reticulate and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[547,653,1896,1921]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6–21. Clypeus and mandibles of females. 6: M. foersteri. 7: M. incana. 8: M. blepharis sp. nov.. 9: M. cinnamomea. 10: M. saussurei. 11: M. nigripes. 12: M. seraxensis. 13: M. ericetorum. 14: M. sanguinipes. 15 (hairs removed on left): M. maxschwarzi sp. nov.. 16 (hairs removed on left): M. flavipes. 17 (hairs removed on left): M. tecta. 18: M. cinnamomea. 19, 20 (profile): M. farinosa. 21: M. riyadhensis (profile). CT: clypeal tooth, APA: apical premarginal area of mandible, HT: clypeal hair tuft, FC: facial comb of hairs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610532/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
); the short and broad, weakly convex clypeus with small preapical medial protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[395,496,1932,1957]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6–21. Clypeus and mandibles of females. 6: M. foersteri. 7: M. incana. 8: M. blepharis sp. nov.. 9: M. cinnamomea. 10: M. saussurei. 11: M. nigripes. 12: M. seraxensis. 13: M. ericetorum. 14: M. sanguinipes. 15 (hairs removed on left): M. maxschwarzi sp. nov.. 16 (hairs removed on left): M. flavipes. 17 (hairs removed on left): M. tecta. 18: M. cinnamomea. 19, 20 (profile): M. farinosa. 21: M. riyadhensis (profile). CT: clypeal tooth, APA: apical premarginal area of mandible, HT: clypeal hair tuft, FC: facial comb of hairs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610532/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
); and the smooth, simple (non-denticulate) apical margin of the clypeus with apical tufts of stiff golden hairs (
<figureCitation box="[452,555,1968,1993]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6–21. Clypeus and mandibles of females. 6: M. foersteri. 7: M. incana. 8: M. blepharis sp. nov.. 9: M. cinnamomea. 10: M. saussurei. 11: M. nigripes. 12: M. seraxensis. 13: M. ericetorum. 14: M. sanguinipes. 15 (hairs removed on left): M. maxschwarzi sp. nov.. 16 (hairs removed on left): M. flavipes. 17 (hairs removed on left): M. tecta. 18: M. cinnamomea. 19, 20 (profile): M. farinosa. 21: M. riyadhensis (profile). CT: clypeal tooth, APA: apical premarginal area of mandible, HT: clypeal hair tuft, FC: facial comb of hairs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610532/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
). Traits shared by males are the multidentate, medially emarginate preapical carina of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[318,428,2004,2029]" captionStart="FIGURES 120–124" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1302,1325]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,481,1281]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1435,481,1281]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 120–124. Diagnostic traits of M. blepharis sp. nov., males. 120: habitus (dorsal view). 121: habitus (lateral view). 122: vertex. 123: metasoma (posterior view). 124: habitus (facial view). LT: lateral tooth, PAC: preapical carina, AMS: apicomedial spine, GF: gonoforceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610552/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Figs 123</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[442,492,2004,2028]" captionStart="FIGURES 125–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1864,1887]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 125–133. Diagnostic traits of M. plumigera sp. nov.. 125: holotype female (facial view). 126: holotype female (lateral view). 127: habitus of male (facial view). 128: habitus of male (lateral view). 129: underside of metasoma of male. 130: vertex of female. 131: vertex of male. 132: genital capsule of male. 133: segments of hind leg of female M. incana (lateral view). LT: lateral tooth, PAC: preapical carina, AMS: apicomedial spine, PVBMS: basomedial spine of penis valve, PVBLA: basolateral angle of penis valve, GF: gonoforceps" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610554/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">129</figureCitation>
); and the erect apicomedial spine of T7 (
<figureCitation box="[995,1103,2004,2029]" captionStart="FIGURES 125–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1864,1887]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[214,1373,193,1842]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 125–133. Diagnostic traits of M. plumigera sp. nov.. 125: holotype female (facial view). 126: holotype female (lateral view). 127: habitus of male (facial view). 128: habitus of male (lateral view). 129: underside of metasoma of male. 130: vertex of female. 131: vertex of male. 132: genital capsule of male. 133: segments of hind leg of female M. incana (lateral view). LT: lateral tooth, PAC: preapical carina, AMS: apicomedial spine, PVBMS: basomedial spine of penis valve, PVBLA: basolateral angle of penis valve, GF: gonoforceps" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610554/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Fig. 129</figureCitation>
). As indicated below, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1937" box="[151,303,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodoleucura">
<emphasis box="[151,303,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">rhodoleucura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group appears to build a morphological transition between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1898" box="[1124,1200,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incana">
<emphasis box="[1124,1200,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">incana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1845" box="[1302,1435,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanipennis">
<emphasis box="[1302,1435,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">cyanipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups. Two species are described here as new and added to the single species hitherto known in the group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">M. incana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One of these new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dorchin &amp; Praz, 2018" authorityName="Dorchin &amp; Praz" authorityYear="2018" box="[554,700,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[554,700,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">M. blepharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,801,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,801,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, also shares a facial comb of modified apically curved hairs (
<figureCitation box="[220,374,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 113–119" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1528,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1508]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,193,1508]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 113–119. Diagnostic traits of M. blepharis sp. nov., females. 113: holotype (dorsal view). 114: holotype (lateral view). 115: vertex. 116: clypeus (profile). 117: holotype (facial view). 118: mesonotum compared with that of 119: M. plumigera sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610550/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">Figs 116, 117</figureCitation>
) and an apicomedial protuberance on the clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[944,1010,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–21" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[164,1421,292,1841]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 6–21. Clypeus and mandibles of females. 6: M. foersteri. 7: M. incana. 8: M. blepharis sp. nov.. 9: M. cinnamomea. 10: M. saussurei. 11: M. nigripes. 12: M. seraxensis. 13: M. ericetorum. 14: M. sanguinipes. 15 (hairs removed on left): M. maxschwarzi sp. nov.. 16 (hairs removed on left): M. flavipes. 17 (hairs removed on left): M. tecta. 18: M. cinnamomea. 19, 20 (profile): M. farinosa. 21: M. riyadhensis (profile). CT: clypeal tooth, APA: apical premarginal area of mandible, HT: clypeal hair tuft, FC: facial comb of hairs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610532/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) with the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1937" box="[1124,1276,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodoleucura">
<emphasis box="[1124,1276,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">rhodoleucura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and with some members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1845" box="[502,635,297,320]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanipennis">
<emphasis box="[502,635,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">cyanipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
